The 26-year-old drifter with a long criminal

record who launched a mute, murderous assault on a California elementary school Tuesday was described by his aunt as a loner and childhood alcoholic, police said.
Purdy, who went by the alias of Patrick West, had lived with an aunt and uncle in Sandy from the first of July until late October, said Sandy Police Chief Fred Punzel.
"I'm shocked.
It's just horrible.
"It troubles me to think that such a terrible thing can happen.
It's like a nightmare.
This sort of thing happens to others, not you.
Stockton is about 15 miles southwest of Lodi.
